-- Caxton CEO Says ElementOne in Bid to Break Control, Business Day Reports
-- Ana Monteiro
-- 2010-09-20T05:42:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/caxton-ceo-says-elementone-in-bid-to-break-control-business-day-reports.html

          
          
             Caxton & CTP Publishers & Printers
Ltd. Chief Executive Officer Terry Moolman said shareholder
Element One Ltd. tried to break up the control structure of the
company, Business Day reported, citing court papers.   
 ElementOne, which is controlled by Allan Gray and
Coronation Fund Managers, took Caxton to court demanding
documents explaining obligations the company has as a Caxton
shareholder, the Johannesburg-based newspaper reported, citing
ElementOne representative Danie Vlok. Moolman said ElementOne
sought the documents to break up the Caxton Group, Business Day
said.  
          
          


  


        